A KANNYWOOD actress Sadiya Haruna has been sentenced to six months in prison for defamation. The sentence, which was handed down by a Kano State High Court on Monday, was without an option of fine. Haruna was found guilty of defamation against one Isa A Isa, her colleague. She reportedly posted a viral video where she alleged that Isa was a homosexual. The actress also referred to Isa as a bastard and an unrepentant womaniser. In August 2021, the actress was convicted of obscenity and indecent dressing by a Kano State Sharia court. She was arraigned before the court by the stateâ€™s Hisbah Board for allegedly sharing sexual content on her social media handles. Haruna was convicted by the presiding judge Ali Jibril Danzaki who thereafter ordered her to attend a Darul Hadith Islamiyya session at Tudun Yola Quarters for six months as the sentence for the offense.